# Welcome to Fixathon!

### Test your skills with PT Application Inspector

In this exciting challenge, your mission is to fix vulnerabilities in an application's business logic. The programmer who built this application wasn't familiar with secure coding practices and left several vulnerabilities in the code. Your goal is to find and fix them to win a prize! Your skills and attention to detail will be the keys to success.

### What's in store for you

You'll have 30 minutes to fix the code:

* Review the vulnerabilities detected by PT Application Inspector.

* Fix as many vulnerabilities as you can.

* Scan the corrected code to ensure the application passes unit tests and that your changes are effective. Good news: there's no limit to the number of scans.

* Minimize the number of vulnerabilities in the application, then scan the code again to lock in your results.

* Complete the task and get some merch if successful

### Tips:

1. Keep an eye on the timer in the bottom right cornerâ€”time is your best friend!

![Timer](data:image/png;base64,)

2. To check your code for vulnerabilities, click the Scan button in the bottom left corner. First, we'll verify the code's integrity with unit tests, and then we'll run our vulnerability scanner.

![Scan](data:image/png;base64,)

3.The detected vulnerabilities will be highlighted in the code as errors, and detailed information about each vulnerability can be found in the PT Application Inspector tab in the Activity Bar.

![PT Application Inspector in the Activity Bar](data:image/png;base64,)

4. If you finish early, click **Finish assignment** in the bottom right corner. You can only submit once, so further edits won't be allowed after submission. The task will automatically end after 30 minutes.

5. You can only get your results after scanning the corrected code. Scanning takes about two minutes, so make sure to leave enough time. If you don't scan the code before the deadline, the task won't countâ€”even if you've fixed all the vulnerabilities.

![Finish assignment](data:image/png;base64,)

### Ready for the challenge? Dive into the world of cybersecurity!
